This paper deals with scheduling and decision-making in an Internet of Things (IoT) system, which involves communication networks, information theory, and control systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves stochastic processes and optimization, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper's focus on decision-making and control systems makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category. Finally, the paper's use of queuing theory and performance analysis is relevant to cs.PF (Performance).
